1 tin Pineapple Slices
1 packet chicken breast
½ lime
2 bunch spring onion
1 cucumber
1 bag herbs
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
olive oil

• Drain and chop pineapple. Cut chicken into 2cm strips
• In a bowl, combine seasoning, chicken and a drizzle of olive oil
• Heat oil in frying pan over high heat
• Cook chicken and pineapple, tossing, until cooked through, 3-4 mins.

• Cut lime into wedges. Thinly slice herbs
• Roughly chop cucumber
• In a second bowl, combine slaw mix, herbs, cucumber and a squeeze of lime juice
• Add a drizzle of oil, season and toss

• Microwave tortillas for 10 second bursts, until warm
• Spread mango mayo over tortillas
• Chop chicken
• Fill tortillas with slaw, chicken and pineapple
• Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.